<item>
            <title>[LU-11399] use separate locks for orphan destroy and objects re-create at OFD</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11399</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11125&quot; title=&quot;ofd_create_hdl() destroys_in_progress already cleared&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-11125&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-11125&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; indicates that there might be contention during recovery process on OFD, when objects are being re-created by resends and orphans are being destroyed at the same time by MDT. Both use os_create_lock mutex but it seems that is not necessary and each process can use own lock. Only the ostid_id should be changed under the same lock.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
